-f,-F:file:This parameter expects a file. This file is then used at nmap with the '-iL' option.
-u,-U:hostname:This parameter expects the same input as nmap without arguments: hostname, ip-address, ip-range, etc.
-n,-N:nmapoption:Use this parameter if you want to use specific nmap arguments. Nmap will still be called with '-A' and '-oA' with its name as defined in output.
-o,-O:output:Use this parameter to name the output xml-file. Default is the name of the given hostname or given file.
-d,-D:directory:Save all the output in this directory. Default is the directory where you call this script from.

-b,-B:blindscan:Use this to have the scan in the background with no output in terminal.ls
